species groups (Note: the morphological structures are drawn in different scales). * – except for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="1999" box="[303,428,1976,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similantis">
<emphasis box="[303,428,1976,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">P. similantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with an indistinctive dorsal spot; ** – formerly the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puplesis &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="1999" box="[966,1115,1976,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrimaculella">
<emphasis box="[966,1115,1976,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">nigrimaculella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group; *** – Mediterranean 
<taxonomicName authority="Stonis &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis &amp; Karsholt, 2021" authorityName="Stonis &amp; Remeikis &amp; Solis &amp; Karsholt" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matrona" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">P. matrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[242,323,2013,2036]" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, described below
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="346" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,466]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
From other groups of Oriental 
<taxonomicName box="[547,717,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,717,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Pseudopostega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[774,850,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frigida">
<emphasis box="[774,850,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">frigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is distinguished by the combination of costal markings of the forewing, and a spiny gnathos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="346" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,466]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
Distribution. Currently the group is comprised of five species distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[1046,1106,223,249]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1117,1187,223,249]" name="Nepal" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1197,1310,223,249]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1320,1432,223,249]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,253,259,285]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[312,398,259,285]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="346" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,466]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
Remarks. Previously, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[448,611,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subviolacea">
<emphasis box="[448,611,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">P. subviolacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was left unplaced in a species group (
<bibRefCitation author="Puplesis, R. &amp; Robinson, G. S." box="[1050,1379,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref11121" refString="Puplesis, R. &amp; Robinson, G. S. (1999) Revision of the Oriental Opostegidae (Lepidoptera) with general comments on phylogeny within the family. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, London, Entomology, 68 (1), 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="1999">Puplesis and Robinson 1999</bibRefCitation>
), but upon re-examination of the female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[687,850,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subviolacea">
<emphasis box="[687,850,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">P. subviolacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we newly attribute this species to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1287,1363,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frigida">
<emphasis box="[1287,1363,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">frigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group because the anal papillae are modified into a single element, a character shared with other species in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1360,1436,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Opostegidae" genus="Pseudopostega" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frigida">
<emphasis box="[1360,1436,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">frigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,466]" box="[199,1407,439,466]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">The presence of modified anal papillae in the female genitalia makes the group distinctive (see Discussion).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
